page.title: 11FRILFORD VILLAGE
page.content:
Frilford is a small village about 2 miles from Marcham. The biggest house is called Beverley House. Frilford has a farm owned by Mr Ford. There are lots of old people in Frilford, but there is no old folks home.
Frilford has two woods. One is owned by the Coopers. The other is owned by the W.I.
Frilford has around six main fields. Five are for crops and the other one is for grazing. Frilford has its own golf course. It is called Frilford Heath Golf Club. Most people would like Frilford.
